headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo’s game is no laughing matter. His jokes? Well, they could use some work.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo's 40 points, late block lead Bucks past 76ers

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 14 of his 32 points in the fourth quarter, and the Chicago Bulls pulled away for a 107-94 victory over the Washington Wizards on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls alone in 5th place after 107-94 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 41 points and the Brooklyn Nets rallied past the Detroit Pistons 130-123 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 41, Nets rally past Pistons 130-123

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 34 points in a triple-double and the Dallas Mavericks routed the Lakers 128-110 on Tuesday night with Los Angeles missing LeBron James because of an ankle issue while anticipating the return of long-injured Anthony Davis.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs rout Lakers 128-110 with LeBron sitting, AD near return

headlines.description: — Paul George's return jolted the Los Angeles Clippers back to life.
headlines.shortLinkText: George returns, Clippers rally in 4th, beat Jazz 121-115
